Repro:

1. Enter the instruction pointer into a `while` loop (example below)
2. Comment out the `while` loop. Hot reload should be triggered.

Expected: Instruction pointer is advanced to the next line after the commented out code.
Actual: The instruction pointer behaves as if it is still inside the (now commented out) `while` loop (ie. continues printing `Attach at ...` in the example below).


```csharp
while (!System.Diagnostics.Debugger.IsAttached)
{
    Console.WriteLine($"Attach at {Environment.ProcessId}"); // Comment out loop and hot reload when this starts printing
    System.Threading.Thread.Sleep(1000);
}

Console.WriteLine("Outside loop");
```

